    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "### Problem\r\nThe `virt_text_hide` option of `nvim_buf_set_extmark` serves two purposes at the same time:\r\n1. Hide the `overlay` virtual text when the extmark is in the text hidden by 'nowrap'\r\n2. Hide the `overlay` virtual text when the extmark is in Visual selection\r\n\r\nAnd it's not possible to only choose one of them.\r\n\r\nFurthermore:\r\n1. With the 'smoothscroll' option, more additions to the `virt_text_hide` option will be needed to control the behavior of virtual text if the extmark is hidden because of 'smoothscroll'.\r\n2. `virt_text_hide` currently only applies to `overlay` virtual text, but one want to make it apply to other types of virtual text as well. E.g. hide `right_align` or `eol` virtual text if the extmark is off the screen.\r\n\r\n### Proposal\r\n\r\nMake the `virt_text_hide` also accept an Dictionary of flags in addition to a Boolean.\r\nSome of the possible flags:\r\n- `visual`: hide the virtual text if the extmark is in Visual selection\r\n- `leftcol`: hide the virtual text if the extmark is hidden because it is to the left of the viewport with 'nowrap'\r\n- `skipcol`: hide the virtual text if the extmark is hidden by 'smoothscroll'\r\n- Some other flag (`rightcol`?) to hide `right_align` or `win_col` virtual text if the extmark is to the right of the viewport?\r\n\r\nIf `true` is passed then enable the four flags mentioned above.\r\n\r\nIf three flags to hide the virtual text of an off-screen extmark is too many, then it may be better to combine them into a single `offscreen` flag.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
